                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="12971859" author="jukkaz" created="Wed, 15 Dec 2010 21:52:46 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Confirmed that this problem still occurs with 1.3.1 and the latest 1.4.0-SNAPSHOT.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13624442" author="msahyoun" created="Sat, 6 Apr 2013 15:36:58 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Confirmed that this problem still occurs with pdfbox-1.8.0&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14021479" author="tilman" created="Sun, 8 Jun 2014 23:07:55 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;It still occurs now, and it is analog to &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PDFBOX-62&quot; title=&quot;Incorrect (zero) character widths returned in some docs&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;PDFBOX-62&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;PDFBOX-62&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; but for type 1 fonts. One possible solution (attached) for this file is to map Arial to the Helvetica AFM file.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14028852" author="lehmi" created="Thu, 12 Jun 2014 05:45:43 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;IMHO the patch is a good workaround, but in the long run we should extend the new FontManager to handle local type1 fonts in a similar way we&apos;ve implemented for true type fonts.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14028880" author="tilman" created="Thu, 12 Jun 2014 06:49:26 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Done as described in rev 1602072 for the trunk and in rev 1602092 for the 1.8 branch.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I don&apos;t have any type1 fonts in my font directory. Maybe on Linux?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14028902" author="jahewson" created="Thu, 12 Jun 2014 07:27:21 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Adobe Acrobat can substitute a TTF/OTF font for a missing Type 1 font, it actually uses Arial.ttf as the replacement for Helvetica. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
